value.title: Mike Pence breaks silence in op-ed slamming House Dems’ voting reform bill
value.excerpt: Pence made his feelings known in an op-ed published Wednesday by The Daily Signal, a blog run by the conservative Heritage Foundation, where the former VP is a fellow.

value.title: Rep. Waltz hits back at Biden: Keeping schools closed is 'Neanderthal thinking'
value.excerpt: Rep. Michael Waltz, R-Fla., pushed back on President Biden for calling out red states for lifting mask mandates.

value.title: Kimmel warns 'canceling' Dr. Seuss is 'how Trump gets reelected': Cancel culture is 'his path to victory'
value.excerpt: ABC late-night host Jimmy Kimmel sounded the alarm on cancel culture Tuesday and how it could help former President Donald Trump get elected again in 2024.

value.title: Florida Gov. DeSantis slams Biden over pace of school reopenings: 'Pathetic failure of leadership'
value.excerpt: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis accused President Biden on Sunday of a “pathetic failure of leadership” for the current pace of his nationwide push to reopen schools during the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: MSNBC contributor: 'My gut's telling me' Trump White House behind lack of Capitol protection on Jan. 6
value.excerpt: MSNBC contributor Frank Figliuzzi speculated Wednesday that the Trump White House delayed sending military assets as the Capitol building was stormed by pro-Trump rioters during the certification of President Biden's election victory.

value.title: McConnell blames Biden’s ‘sweeping left-wing amnesty plan' for fueling border surge
value.excerpt: Senate GOP Leader Mitch McConnell on Wednesday blamed President Biden’s “sweeping left-wing amnesty plan” for fueling the escalating migrant crisis on the southern border -- and said it sidelined the interests of American workers.

value.title: Pence rails against HR 1, laments Capitol riot prevented 'substantive discussion' on election integrity
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence offered harsh criticism for a Democrat-proposed voting reform legislation while condemning the Capitol protest on Jan. 6 that, he said, interrupted what would have been a worthwhile discussion of election integrity.

value.title: Rep. Crenshaw slams Biden's border policy: 'Prioritizing illegal immigrants over US citizens’
value.excerpt: Rep. Dan Crenshaw, R-Texas, says he believes the Biden administration’s immigration policies are "prioritizing illegal immigrants over U.S. citizens."

value.title: Kamala Harris’ tweet about Dr. Seuss resurfaces amid racial controversy
value.excerpt: Harris was a senator when she sent out the tweet, dated March 2, 2017, in which she wished the famed children’s book author a happy birthday.

value.title: Flashback: Gov. Cuomo in 2018 assailed 'disrespect for women' by 'sexist and disgusting' Trump administration

value.title: Biden administration argues migrant surge is a 'challenge,' not a 'crisis'
value.excerpt: President Biden is declining to call the situation at the southern border a crisis – even amid reports that his administration needs another 20,000 beds at migrant facilities to deal with a surge of unaccompanied minors.

value.title: Psaki pressed on whether Biden admin taking credit for Trump accomplishments on vaccine partnership

value.title: Biden directs states to prioritize educators in vaccine rollouts as he aims to reopen schools
value.excerpt: President Biden on Tuesday announced a new effort to vaccinate educators and childcare workers as a means to accelerate the safe reopening of schools.

value.title: Trumps received COVID-19 vaccines at White House in January
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump and former first lady Melania Trump received their COVID-19 vaccines in January at the White House, Fox News confirmed.

value.title: MacCallum presses Buttigieg: 'As a responsible person,' how could you support Biden COVID relief plan?
value.excerpt: Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg defended his support of President Biden’s $1.9 trillion COVID-19 relief plan on Monday, dismissing Republican complaints over Democratic pet projects and unrelated items included in the legislation.

value.title: Laid-off pipeline worker: The Biden administration ‘has taken my livelihood from me’
value.excerpt: Jason Jernigan, a laid-off Keystone XL Pipeline worker, told "America’s Newsroom" on Monday that he doesn’t know how he is going to make a living now, saying, "This is all I know how to do."

value.title: Biden supports 'independent review' of Cuomo sexual harassment claims ‒ something Tara Reade never got
value.excerpt: Gov. Cuomo's office denied Lindsey Boylan's harassment claims, calling them "simply false."

value.title: Katrina Pierson, Trump presidential campaign veteran, moves toward congressional bid in Texas
value.excerpt: The field of Republicans running to succeed the late Republican Rep. Ron Wright of Texas is growing. Katrina Pierson, who served as a top adviser on President Trump’s 2016 and 2020 campaigns, is gearing up to launch a campaign, two sources with knowledge of her planning confirmed to Fox News.

value.title: Former Trump campaign communications director Murtaugh joining Heritage Foundation
value.excerpt: Former Trump campaign communications director Tim Murtaugh is joining the Heritage Foundation and launching his own public affairs firm, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Trump pays tribute to Rush Limbaugh at CPAC speech: 'Irreplaceable'
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump on Sunday paid tribute to the late radio legend Rush Limbaugh, who was long considered the voice of the conservative movement and who was one of the first high-profile right-wing media personalities to back Trump's first presidential run.

value.title: Sen. Scott says he will support incumbent GOP senators over Trump-backed primary challengers
value.excerpt: Sen. Rick Scott, R-Fl., chair of the National Republican Senatorial Committee, told "Fox News Sunday" that he will support any incumbent Republican senator against primary challengers, even if that challenge is supported by former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Pompeo says Biden administration sending ‘mixed signals’ on China's human rights abuses
value.excerpt: Former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Saturday that the Biden administration has sent "mixed signals" on the Chinese persecution of religious minorities in Xinjiang -- and called for the administration to impose "real costs" on Beijing.

value.title: Steve Hilton: Kamala Harris silent on Cuomo allegations after ‘grandstanding’ at Kavanaugh hearings
value.excerpt: “The focus should be on Vice President Kamala Harris” amid the sexual harassment allegations against N.Y. Gov. Andrew Cuomo, Fox News “The Revolution” host Steve Hilton said on Friday.

value.title: Ted Cruz in CPAC speech says ‘Trump ain’t goin’ anywhere,’ jokes about Cancun controversy
value.excerpt: Sen. Ted Cruz says the GOP is the party of the working class and vows that former President Trump will remain a power player in the Republican Party.

value.title: Biden's Syria airstrike earns applause from prominent Republicans
value.excerpt: Following the airstrike ordered by Biden against Iranian-backed militia members Thursday night, House Foreign Affairs Committee ranking member Rep. Michael McCaul, R-Texas, and Rep. French Hill, R-Ark., applauded the successful airstrike.

value.title: Corey Lewandowski likely to lead new Trump political action committee
value.excerpt: Former President Trump is starting up a new political action committee and is eyeing longtime top political adviser and aide Corey Lewandowski to head up the new super PAC, multiple people with knowledge of the conversations confirmed to Fox News.

value.title: Biden administration and Democrats 'do not care' about American jobs: Sen. Scott
value.excerpt: Sen. Rick Scott R-Fla. said Friday that the Biden administration and Democrats "don't care about jobs" and that the attempted inclusion of a $15 minimum wage in the latest coronavirus stimulus bill is just "payback" to liberal Democrats.
